-- Visa Board Appoints Matschullat Chairman as Saunders Retires
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-01-30T03:47:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-30/visa-board-appoints-matschullat-chairman-as-saunders-retires.html
Visa Inc. (V) ’s board of directors named
Robert W. Matschullat as independent, non-executive chairman of
the world’s largest payments network.  Matschullat’s appointment, which takes effect April 1,
follows the retirement of Executive Chairman Joseph W. Saunders,
the Foster City, California-based company said in a statement
distributed by  Business Wire . Matschullat, a former chairman of
Clorox Co., has been a Visa director since 2007, according to
the statement.  Matschullat “possesses a wealth of experience in global
consumer products and corporate finance that has been of great
benefit to the board and the company,” Saunders said in the
statement.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
